SELECT SUM(COALESCE("order total paid", 0)) AS valor_recebido
    FROM receivables_db.report_orders;

SELECT 
        SUM(
            COALESCE("contract total value expected", 0) - 
            COALESCE("order total paid", 0)
        ) AS valor_deixado_de_receber
    FROM 
        receivables_db.report_orders
    WHERE 
        status = 'EARLY PURCHASE';

pergunta_texto: Comparar vendas deste ms com o ms passado?
sql_aprovada:
WITH vendas_mes_atual AS (
        SELECT COUNT(*) AS total
        FROM receivables_db.report_orders
        WHERE TRY(
            CAST(
                date_parse(TRIM("contract start date"), '%Y-%m-%d %I:%i %p') AS TIMESTAMP
            )
        ) BETWEEN date_trunc('month', current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York')
          AND date_trunc('month', current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York') + interval '1' month - interval '1' day
    ),
    vendas_mes_passado AS (
        SELECT COUNT(*) AS total
        FROM receivables_db.report_orders
        WHERE TRY(
            CAST(
                date_parse(TRIM("contract start date"), '%Y-%m-%d %I:%i %p') AS TIMESTAMP
            )
        ) BETWEEN date_trunc('month', date_add('month', -1, current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York'))
          AND date_trunc('month', current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York')
    )
    SELECT 
        vendas_mes_atual.total AS vendas_mes_atual,
        vendas_mes_passado.total AS vendas_mes_passado
    FROM vendas_mes_atual
    CROSS JOIN vendas_mes_passado;

pergunta_texto: traga-me a quantidade de vendas nos ltimos 3 meses (total e tambm o total de vendas em cada ms)
sql_aprovada:
WITH vendas_por_mes AS (
        SELECT 
            date_trunc(
                'month', 
                TRY(CAST(date_parse(TRIM("contract start date"), '%Y-%m-%d %I:%i %p') AS TIMESTAMP))
            ) AS mes,
            COUNT(*) AS total_vendas
        FROM 
            receivables_db.report_orders
        WHERE 
            TRY(CAST(date_parse(TRIM("contract start date"), '%Y-%m-%d %I:%i %p') AS TIMESTAMP)) BETWEEN 
                date_trunc('month', date_add('month', -3, current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York'))
                AND 
                date_trunc('month', current_timestamp AT TIME ZONE 'America/New_York') + interval '1' month - interval '1' day
        GROUP BY 
            date_trunc(
                'month', 
                TRY(CAST(date_parse(TRIM("contract start date"), '%Y-%m-%d %I:%i %p') AS TIMESTAMP))
            )
    )
    SELECT 
        mes,
        total_vendas,
        SUM(total_vendas) OVER () AS total_vendas_3_meses
    FROM 
        vendas_por_mes
    ORDER BY 
        mes;
